"mesh:D016202"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "NMDA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984937906265259, "span": {"begin": 719, "end": 723}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2902"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NMDA receptor", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9785531163215637, "span": {"begin": 719, "end": 732}}], "text": "Status epilepticus induced by exposure to soman in guinea pigs either reduced or arrested after treatment with MK-801, an NMDA receptor antagonist, or was prevented entirely by pretreatment with MK-801 (Sparenborg et al., 1992). An earlier experiment under the same conditions showed similar results (Braitman and Sparenborg, 1989).  Status epilepticus was induced through electrical stimulation in 13&ndash;15-week-old male Wistar rats and was successfully terminated using MK-801 (Mazarati and Wasterlain, 1999).  Adult male Sprague-Dawley rats had status epilepticus induced through electrical stimulation which was shown to be refractory to GABAergic drugs, but was still successfully terminated using ketamine, an NMDA receptor antagonist (Borris et al., 2000).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:15:37 +0000 2026"}